The important error is this:

error: implicit declaration of function 'open_with_fake_path'

This means the VirtualBox kernel module source is not compatible with your current RHEL 9.8 kernel (5.14.0-687.22.1.el9_8.x86_64). The build fails before the vboxdrv module can be created.

Your system currently has:

Kernel: 5.14.0-687.22.1.el9_8.x86_64 (RHEL 9.8)

VirtualBox: 7.2.12


This is not a missing kernel-devel or gcc problem—the kernel API has changed, and the VirtualBox source you're using doesn't compile against it.

First, verify prerequisites

Run:

rpm -q kernel-devel-$(uname -r)
rpm -q kernel-headers-$(uname -r)
rpm -q gcc make elfutils-libelf-devel

All should report as installed.

If they are installed

The solution is to use a VirtualBox build that supports your kernel.

You have two options:

1. Upgrade VirtualBox to the newest release available from Oracle (preferred).


2. Boot an older RHEL kernel that VirtualBox 7.2.12 supports, if one is still installed.



Also check whether Secure Boot is enabled

mokutil --sb-state

If it says SecureBoot enabled, even a successfully built module must be signed before it can load.

I need one more output

Please run:

dnf list installed kernel\*

This will show whether you have an older kernel available that you can boot temporarily, or whether upgrading VirtualBox is the only practical solution.
